<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION, SINGLE SPEED AXLES: SPICER D135-S,
        F155-S, F170-S SERIES - DISASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc id="hl1401403" svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="8">
            <title>DIFFERENTIAL</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401411">Figure 11.</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401411" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401411" filename="../figg14/g1401411.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Differential - Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Match mark differential case halves with punch or chisel for correct alignment in
                    reassembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401412">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401412" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401412" filename="../figg14/g1401412.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Marking Differential Case</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove differential case bolts and self- locking nuts, and lift off the right hand case
                    half (left,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401413">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401413" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401413" filename="../figg14/g1401413.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13. Removing Differential Case</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove thrust washer and differential side gear (right,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401413">Figure 13</hotlnk>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift out cross shaft, pinion mates and thrust washers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401414">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401414" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401414" filename="../figg14/g1401414.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Removing Cross Shaft, Pinion Mates &#38; Thrust Washers</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove second differential side gear and thrust washer (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401415">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401415" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401415" filename="../figg14/g1401415.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15. Side Gear &#38; Thrust Washer Removal</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If differential side bearings are to be replaced, remove old bearings using suitable
                    puller
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401416">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401416" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401416" filename="../figg14/g1401416.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Remove Old Bearings</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Inspect all parts, including the machined surfaces of case itself.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>If any gears are to be replaced, they must be replaced in sets. Inspect thrust washers for
                            scoring and excessive wear. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When it is necessary to remove ring gear from differential case, carefully center punch
                    each rivet head. Use a 7/16" drill bit for the D135-S rivets and a 9/16" drill bit for the F155-S
                    and F170-S rivets. Drill through rivet heads (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401417">Figure 17</hotlnk>). Next, use a rounded type punch to drive out the
                    remaining portion of the rivet.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401417" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401417" filename="../figg14/g1401417.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Punching Rivet Heads</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Always use a soft metal hammer or H.D. plastic head hammer to strike punch.</para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Wear safe eye protection. Do not hit steel parts with a steel hammer. Parts can break and
                            cause injury.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Do not use a chisel to remove rivet heads, as damage to differential case may result.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When re-installing the ring gear to the differential case, use a hydraulic or mechanical
                    press and suitable riveting fixture (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401418">Figure 18</hotlnk>). Pressure requirement per rivet is 20 to 25 U.S. tons
                    (18.1 to 22.7 metric tons) for the D135-S, and 45 to 50 U.S. tons (41 to 45 metric tons) for the
                    F155-S and F170-S.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401418" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401418" filename="../figg14/g1401418.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 18. Riveting Fixture for Re-installing Ring Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
